The People’s Democratic Party (PDP) National Youth Movement (NYM), South-West zone on Tuesday called on the National Chairman of the party, Iyorchia Ayu, members of the National Working Committee (NWC) and other stakeholders to go for a true reconciliation among warring factions. The Youth Movement in a statement made by its Vice President, Olanrewaju Mosaku said that such a move will be a way of improving the party’s chances in the 2023 general election. Speaking at the inauguration of its zonal executive in Abeokuta, Ogun State, Mosaku insisted that only true reconciliation would unite the party and guarantee its victory in 2023. He hinted that the group is poised to position the youths ahead of the forthcoming general elections while calling for the need to improve the party’s chances by starting “in our tertiary institutions, football viewing centres, clubs, bars, our streets and so on.” He said “As youths, we are the pillar of the party and our country Nigeria, therefore we breed to take charge, start from the front and willing to continue from where the stakeholders stop in order for us to fully participate in the governance system of the country in various positions in the government. “The success of our party lies in our hands, we must play our role diligently and judiciously for us to return back to governance at the Federal and States Level.”